Mission.Author: KingRaptor
Mission.Name: Sunrise Episode 8E - The King is Dead

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Dereg") for unitID in pairs(units) do GG.CAI.RemoveUnit(unitID) end for i=1,3 do GG.CAI.SuspendAI(i, true) if i== 2 then GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(i, UnitDefNames.factoryamph.id, 0) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(i, UnitDefNames.factorycloak.id, 0) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(i, UnitDefNames.factoryshield.id, 0) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(i, UnitDefNames.factoryhover.id, 0) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(i, UnitDefNames.factoryjump.id, 0) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(i, UnitDefNames.factoryspider.id, 0) end end
local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Tomb") GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, true)
units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Screamer") for unitID in pairs(units) do Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.STOCKPILE, {}, { "ctrl", "shift" }) end

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("March") local x, z = 8470, 6760 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x, z) Spring.GiveOrderToUnitMap(units, CMD.MOVE, {x, y, z}, {"ctrl"})

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Traitors, rebels and heretics, hear my words!
You have come for the Emperor, but all you will find here is your death.
You trespass on his soil, lay waste to his works, and now you seek to defile his very throne.
Now the Emperor rises, and His wrath shall shake the galaxy!
Our will is resolute. Our faith is limitless. Our vengeance shall know no bounds.
Ready yourselves, foes of the Empire, for today is your judgement day!

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Cutscene2") for unitID in pairs(units) do local ux, uy, uz = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID) local x, z = ux - 400, uz - 400 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x, z) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.ATTACK, {x, y, z}, 0) end
for i=1,3 do GG.CAI.SuspendAI(i, false) end

TriggerLogic.Message: You're late. The battle's already started.
I got here as fast as we could. How are we holding up?
Like a jumper halfway down the building. Now hurry up and secure a beachhead, the Imperials aren't gonna wait for us.

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description:
Use your naval units to destroy the enemy base at our landing site. Neutralize their factory, fusion reactors and any heavy defenses present.
The Battleship must remain alive until this task is complete.
TriggerLogic.Title: Clear Beachhead

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: Destroy all defenses around the Emperor's tomb and secure it.
TriggerLogic.Title: Secure Throne

TriggerLogic.Description: Eliminate the Praetorian Prefect, Scipio Astra, for good.
TriggerLogic.Title: Kill Scipio Astra

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local units = Spring.GetUnitsInCylinder(6090, 5590, 750) local pwUnits = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("PW") local secure = 1
for i=1,#units do local unitID = units[i] local teamID = Spring.GetUnitTeam(unitID) if teamID == 2 or teamID == 3 then if not pwUnits[unitID] then secure = 0 break end end end
if secure == 1 and GG.mission.counters["Hill Secure"] == 0 then GG.mission.ExecuteTriggerByName("Hill Secured") elseif secure == 0 and GG.mission.counters["Hill Secure"] == 1 then GG.mission.ExecuteTriggerByName("Hill Unsecured") end

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Beach assault failed. Switching to secondary insertion point.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: We need to secure the Emperor's tomb on that hill. Do whatever it takes.

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: Eliminate the Praetorian Prefect, Scipio Astra, for good.
TriggerLogic.Title: Kill Scipio Astra

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: Destroy all defenses around the Emperor's tomb and secure it.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Ada") GG.GiveFacplop(unitID)

-- spawn Goliaths local adaID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Ada") local tx, ty, tz = Spring.GetUnitPosition(adaID)
local x, z local altPos = GG.mission.counters["Using Alt Insertion"] == 1 if altPos then x,z = 7440, 3000 else x,z = 3460, 7200 end local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x,z)
for i=1,2 do local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("corgol", x, y, z, altPos and "w" or "e", 2) Spring.SpawnCEG("teleport_in", x, y, z) GG.mission.AddUnitGroup(unitID, "Goliath") GG.CAI.RemoveUnit(unitID) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.MOVE, {tx, ty, tz}, 0)
x = x + 128 z = z + 128 y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x,z) end
-- spawn gnats if altPos then x = Game.mapSizeX + 256 z = - 384 else x = -256 z = Game.mapSizeZ + 384 end
local dx = altPos and -3200 or 3200 local dz = -dx
for i=1,10 do unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("bladew", x, 50, z, altPos and "n" or "s", 0) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x, z) local mx, mz = x + dx, z + dz local my = Spring.GetGroundHeight(mx, mz) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIGHT, {mx, my, mz}, 0)
x = x + 64 z = z + 64 if i == 4 or i == 5 then GG.mission.AddUnitGroup(unitID, "Gnat") end end

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: We've got heavy units inbound. Gnats can stunlock them for your command unit's disintegrator to blow out of existence.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message: The Gnat is a light drone with an inaccurate stunner weapon that can nevertheless lock down heavy enemy units in fairly short order. Vulnerable to most ground weapons.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: My word... that's a Detriment.
Nothing less to defend the Emperor's tomb. It'll take a lot of concentrated firepower to bring that thing down.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local altPos = GG.mission.counters["Using Alt Insertion"] == 1
local x, z if altPos then x = Game.mapSizeX + 512 z = -512 else x = -512 z = Game.mapSizeZ + 512 end
local dx = altPos and -3200 or 3200 local dz = -dx
local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("corcrw", x, 50, z, altPos and "n" or "s", 0) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x, z) local mx, mz = x + dx, z + dz local my = Spring.GetGroundHeight(mx, mz) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIGHT, {mx, my, mz}, 0)
GG.mission.AddUnitGroup(unitID, "Krow")

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Some heavy air firepower might help us breach their defenses. I'm sending you Krow flying fortesses, Ada.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message: The Krow flying fortress is an ultra-heavy gunship with three powerful pulse weapons and the ability to carpet bomb the area directly under it. Use it to sweep in, wipe out a concentration of enemies, and break engagement before it takes too much damage, then repair and repeat.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: The enemy has three antinuke defense structures around the peak. If we can take them out, we can blow out the defenses with a nuclear missile or three.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message: The Silencer ICBM silo stockpiles nuclear missiles at the cost of metal, energy and time. Just one of these can blow most armies and bases out of existence, but antinuke units can intercept them, and heavy units can survive a nuclear blast with HP to spare.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Face me, murderer! In the Emperor's name, I shall avenge the Legate Fidus!
Interesting. I didn't think you cared, prefect.
He was a friend, you... you...
I didn't kill him, Astra. Your fallen Empire did... just as it will kill you.
Enough! Devil take you, traitor!
Why won't you just die, Ada Caedmon?!
I didn't get thrown a thousand years into the future to die here, Astra. Not while I have my past to reclaim.
You have no past, demon-spawn. And no future.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local scipioAstraID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("ScipioAstra") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(scipioAstraID, true) Spring.SetUnitHealth(scipioAstraID, {paralyze = 999999}) GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(scipioAstraID, true) Spring.SetUnitPosition(scipioAstraID, x, z) Spring.MoveCtrl.Enable(scipioAstraID) -- clear impulse Spring.MoveCtrl.Disable(scipioAstraID)
-- clear attack commands on the now-dead Scipio Astra local units = Spring.GetUnitsInCylinder(x, z, 700)
local blankTable = {} for i=1,#units do local unitID = units[i] local queue = Spring.GetUnitCommands(unitID, 1) or blankTable local cmd = queue[1] if cmd and cmd.id == CMD.ATTACK and cmd.params[1] == scipioAstraID then Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.REMOVE, {cmd.tag}, 0) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, 34924, blankTable, 0) -- cancel target Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.WAIT, blankTable, 0) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.WAIT, blankTable, 0) end end
local camID = Spring.CreateUnit("fakeunit_los", x, y, z, "s", 0) GG.mission.AddUnitGroup(camID, "DeathCam")
local units = Spring.GetTeamUnits(0) for i=1,#units do GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(units[i], true) end

local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("ScipioAstra") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID, true) x = x + math.random(-15, 15) z = z + math.random(-15, 15) y = y + math.random(-20, 20) Spring.SpawnCEG("babette", x, y, z)

TriggerLogic.Message: NO! Emperor curse you, Ada Caedmon...
Your Majesty... I'm sorry...

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local units = Spring.GetTeamUnits(0) for i=1,#units do GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(units[i], false) end
if GG.mission.counters["Hill Secure"] == 1 then GG.mission.ExecuteTriggerByName("Ending") end

local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Ada") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID, true) Spring.SpawnCEG("gate", x, y, z) Spring.SpawnCEG("teleport_out", x, y, z) Spring.PlaySoundFile("sounds/misc/teleport.wav", 2.0, x, y, z, nil, nil, nil, "sfx") Spring.DestroyUnit(unitID, false, true)

if GG.mission.counters["Scipio Astra Dead"] == 1 then GG.mission.ExecuteTriggerByName("Ending") end

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Those defenses appear to be drawing energy directly from the artefact itself. We won't be able to disconnect their power supply.
Then we take them down the hard way.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: If the ground gets too chewed up for vehicles to pass, have a constructor restore the terrain.

TriggerLogic.Message: And so... an era ends.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Ada") if unitID then GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, true) end

for i=1,3 do GG.CAI.SuspendAI(i, true) end
local pwUnits = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("PW") local adaID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Ada")
local hillUnits = Spring.GetAllUnits() --Spring.GetUnitsInCylinder(6090, 5590, 2500) for i=1,#hillUnits do local unitID = hillUnits[i] if not (unitID == adaID or pwUnits[unitID]) then Spring.DestroyUnit(unitID, false, true) else GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, true) end end
Spring.SetUnitPosition(adaID, 6090, 5890) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(adaID, CMD.FIRE_STATE, {0}, 0) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(adaID, CMD.STOP, {}, 0)
local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Tomb") GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, false) Spring.SetUnitMaxHealth(unitID, 2000)
unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("EndDestruction") Spring.SetUnitNeutral(unitID, true) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIRE_STATE, {0}, 0)

TriggerLogic.Description: What will you do? ... Become the Empress? ... Renounce the Empire? ... or burn it all to the ground?
TriggerLogic.Title: Choose your Destiny

TriggerLogic.Message: It's done.
...Damn. I think he's been dead longer than I was out.
Well now, friend Ada. What will you do?
